{[show S]After a Jacoby transfer, partner can raise to 4NT. With a known fit the 1NT opener counts the trump support as extra and accepts in the suit, not in notrump.
[BID 1N] You open 1NT, fifteen to seventeen balanced. Your partner bids 2\D, a Jacoby transfer showing five or more hearts and asking opener to bid the suit.
[BID 2H] You complete the transfer with 2\H. Your partner raises to 4NT, a quantitative slam invitation; with a fit located, opener may accept in hearts.
[BID 6H] A known heart fit adds playing strength, so you accept the invitation in the suit and bid 6\H.
[show NS]South's fifteen would pass a quantitative raise with no fit, but four-card support for the transfer makes a nine-card fit and an extra trick, so accepting in 6H is right; it makes. The fit, not the point count, tips this decision.}
